27/06/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- BiH Presidency Chairman Borislav Paravac, Croatian President Stipe Mesic and Serbia-Montenegro President Svetozar Marovic meet in Belgrade Monday (27 June) under the so-called Igman Initiative, uniting the signatories of the Dayton Peace Accords. Paravac, Mesic and Marovic are expected to sign a joint declaration for enhancement of mutual dialogue and co-operation, support of refugee returns and visa regime liberalisation. (RTS, Danas Blic, Beta, Tanjug - 27/06/05; RTRS, Tanjug - 26/06/05)
